            <p>Congregation Moses Montefiore&#44;<lb/>
                160 EAST 112TH STREET.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; Elul 29&#45;&#45;5650.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr. S. Morais&#44;<lb/>
                Philadelphia.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir&#33;<lb/></p>
            <p>At the suggestion of<lb/> Dr. B. Drachman&#44; our Board of<lb/> Trustees&#44; a few weeks ago&#44; secured<lb/> the services of Mr. Jos. H. Herts<lb/> &#40;a student in your theological semi&#45;<lb/>nary&#41; to preach in our synagogue<lb/> during the ensuing holy&#45;days.  Our<lb/> congregation was duly apprised of<lb/> this by a public announcement.<lb/>  From a letter&#44; however&#44; received on<lb/> the 12th Inst. dated the day before&#44;<lb/> Mr. Herts writes to Mr. A. E. Hartsgensis<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>that he is unable to <sic>fulfil</sic> his promise<lb/> with us&#44; having been informed that<lb/> Mr. Blumenthal&#44; Dr. Cohen and<lb/> yourself do not think it proper<lb/> that a young man of his age<lb/> should appear in the pulpit on<lb/> &#91;Hebrew&#93;.  This is substan&#45;<lb/>tially&#44; if not <sic>litterally</sic>&#44; what he<lb/> wrote.<lb/></p>
            <p>Had we received earlier<lb/> notification of the disapproval<lb/> of Mr. Herts&#39; engagement with<lb/> us&#44; we might&#44; possibly&#44; have<lb/> sought elsewhere for a substitute&#44;<lb/> but coming&#44; as it does&#44; at the<lb/> eleventh hour&#44; it places us in<lb/> a very embarrassing position.<lb/></p>
            <p>Our sole object in writing to<lb/> you is to acquaint you with<lb/> all the facts in the case.<lb/></p>
            <p>Accept our friendly greetings<lb/> of the season&#59; and believe us.<lb/> very respectfully.<lb/> your.<lb/> Isidore Osorio.<lb/> Board of Trustees  Secretary of the<lb/></p>
            <p>616 Spruce</p>
            </body>
    </text>
